WEBVTT

1
00:01:36.830 --> 00:01:39.375
- Go. go. go. go!
- Move it. move it!

2
00:01:39.458 --> 00:01:41.085
- Let's go. let's go!
- Come on!

3
00:01:42.002 --> 00:01:43.212
It's a powder keg in there.

4
00:01:43.295 --> 00:01:45.673
No one moves till we get word
from the mayor.

5
00:01:58.936 --> 00:02:00.646
Shoot! Hey.

6
00:02:00.729 --> 00:02:01.939
Hey.

7
00:02:02.022 --> 00:02:03.357
Hey. Little girl.

8
00:02:03.983 --> 00:02:05.317
Stop.

9
00:02:05.734 --> 00:02:06.735
Stop!

10
00:02:08.821 --> 00:02:10.030
Stay down!

11
00:02:21.584 --> 00:02:23.294
What do you want. little one?

12
00:02:25.921 --> 00:02:27.172
Your ass.

13
00:02:53.490 --> 00:02:54.491
Boo!

14
00:03:15.095 --> 00:03:16.096
Well done.

15
00:03:36.659 --> 00:03:37.660
Who...

16
00:03:38.160 --> 00:03:39.328
who are you?

17
00:03:40.329 --> 00:03:42.581
Frank Drebin. Police Squad.

18
00:03:44.041 --> 00:03:45.334
The new version.

19
00:04:03.477 --> 00:04:04.603
Shoot.

20
00:04:16.699 --> 00:04:20.828
My name is Sergeant Frank Drebin.
Detective Lieutenant. Police Squad.

21
00:04:20.911 --> 00:04:23.497
a special division of the LAPD.

22
00:04:23.580 --> 00:04:26.709
The day after the bank robbery
started like any other.

23
00:04:26.792 --> 00:04:29.503
I woke up in my empty cop apartment.

24
00:04:29.586 --> 00:04:32.339
stared at a picture
of my deceased cop wife

25
00:04:32.423 --> 00:04:34.758
and choked back cop tears.

26
00:04:34.842 --> 00:04:37.010
A perfect morning? Sure.

27
00:04:37.094 --> 00:04:40.097
But I had no idea what this city
had in store for me.

28
00:04:42.182 --> 00:04:43.183
What the hell?

29
00:04:45.769 --> 00:04:47.062
- Hey!
- There he is.

30
00:04:47.146 --> 00:04:48.397
Way to go. Frank!

31
00:04:50.899 --> 00:04:52.401
Thank you. Thanks. everyone.

32
00:04:52.484 --> 00:04:53.485
What is this?

33
00:04:53.569 --> 00:04:55.195
Don't cheer for him!

34
00:04:55.279 --> 00:04:57.406
You two. my office now!

35
00:05:00.993 --> 00:05:04.788
Thanks to you. I just spent two hours
getting chewed out by the mayor.

36
00:05:04.872 --> 00:05:08.041
Apparently. some of the bank robbers
you put in the ICU.

37
00:05:08.125 --> 00:05:10.586
they're lawyering up to sue the city.

38
00:05:10.669 --> 00:05:12.629
That's ridiculous. They're criminals.

39
00:05:12.713 --> 00:05:13.714
It's the law.

40
00:05:13.797 --> 00:05:15.758
Since when do cops
have to follow the law?

41
00:05:15.841 --> 00:05:17.259
- Since forever.
- Yeah?

42
00:05:17.342 --> 00:05:19.595
And who's going to arrest me?
Other cops?

43
00:05:19.678 --> 00:05:20.804
- Yes.
- Is she serious?

44
00:05:20.888 --> 00:05:22.306
Is he serious?

45
00:05:22.389 --> 00:05:23.682
He's... No.

46
00:05:23.766 --> 00:05:25.267
Look. let me be crystal clear.

47
00:05:25.350 --> 00:05:28.687
They are threatening to shut down
Police Squad because of you.

48
00:05:28.771 --> 00:05:31.231
Honestly. you're lucky
you still work here

49
00:05:31.315 --> 00:05:33.358
after last year's McDonald's incident.

50
00:05:33.442 --> 00:05:35.444
They wouldn't sell me Freedom Fries.

51
00:05:35.527 --> 00:05:38.947
- You arrested the entire staff!
- I wasn't thinking clearly.

52
00:05:39.573 --> 00:05:42.493
I was furious
about the Janet Jackson Super Bowl.

53
00:05:42.576 --> 00:05:44.495
That was 20 years ago!

54
00:05:44.578 --> 00:05:45.704
Not to me.

55
00:05:45.788 --> 00:05:47.623
We understand. Chief.
You're right.

56
00:05:47.706 --> 00:05:48.707
Good.

57
00:05:48.791 --> 00:05:50.542
'Cause I'm taking you
off the bank job.

58
00:05:50.626 --> 00:05:53.337
- What?
- I'm putting you on collisions.

59
00:05:53.420 --> 00:05:55.506
There's a crash up in Malibu.

60
00:05:55.589 --> 00:05:57.049
Yes. ma'am. Thank you.

61
00:05:57.132 --> 00:06:00.302
And make sure your bodycams
are actually turned on!

62
00:06:01.345 --> 00:06:04.014
Got it. Camera will be on.

63
00:06:06.934 --> 00:06:08.310
Drebin!

64
00:06:08.393 --> 00:06:10.687
It's a new day at Police Squad!

65
00:06:13.023 --> 00:06:15.359
Things are changing so fast
around here.

66
00:06:16.026 --> 00:06:18.195
I guess you really
can't fight City Hall. huh?

67
00:06:18.278 --> 00:06:19.863
No. It's a building.

68
00:06:21.031 --> 00:06:22.366
Now. there's a real man.

69
00:06:23.951 --> 00:06:26.203
They just don't make 'em
like your pops anymore.

70
00:06:26.662 --> 00:06:29.581
I'm glad he's not around
to see what Police Squad has come to.

71
00:06:30.624 --> 00:06:32.543
Mind if I take a minute. Ed?

72
00:06:32.626 --> 00:06:33.752
Of course.

73
00:06:37.923 --> 00:06:40.050
Hi. Daddy. It's me. Frank Jr.

74
00:06:41.385 --> 00:06:43.095
I want to be just like you. but...

75
00:06:43.720 --> 00:06:47.182
at the same time.
be completely different and original.

76
00:06:47.266 --> 00:06:49.309
So. if you're proud of me.

77
00:06:49.977 --> 00:06:51.478
give me a sign. like...

78
00:06:52.062 --> 00:06:54.982
maybe make me see an owl or something.

79
00:06:56.567 --> 00:06:57.568
Hey. Dad.

80
00:06:58.735 --> 00:07:00.028
It's me. Ed.

81
00:07:01.822 --> 00:07:03.365
Boy. do I miss you.

82
00:07:07.494 --> 00:07:08.662
Hey. Pops.

83
00:07:16.461 --> 00:07:20.048
Ed and I pulled up to the Malibu
car crash around 2:00 p.m.

84
00:07:20.549 --> 00:07:21.592
Nothing unusual.

85
00:07:22.134 --> 00:07:25.888
But in this city.
usual is unusual... usually.

86
00:07:25.971 --> 00:07:26.972
What the hell?

87
00:07:29.308 --> 00:07:31.476
So how was your date
last night. Frank?

88
00:07:32.311 --> 00:07:33.979
I couldn't go through with it.

89
00:07:34.062 --> 00:07:35.522
- You canceled?
- Nope.

90
00:07:36.023 --> 00:07:37.107
I didn't want to upset her.

91
00:07:37.190 --> 00:07:40.319
so I had Officer Barnes
tell her I was stabbed to death.

92
00:07:40.402 --> 00:07:41.653
You're a real romantic. Frank.

93
00:07:41.737 --> 00:07:44.781
But everyone needs someone.
even a widower like you.

94
00:07:44.865 --> 00:07:47.784
I'm just not ready
to open myself to love again.

95
00:07:48.285 --> 00:07:50.871
I had them wait to clear the wreck
so you could get eyes on it.

96
00:07:50.954 --> 00:07:52.414
Crash happened around 4:00 a.m.

97
00:07:52.497 --> 00:07:55.000
Well. there are no skid marks
on the road.

98
00:07:55.584 --> 00:07:58.086
He didn't hit the brakes
before going over.

99
00:07:58.170 --> 00:07:59.254
Drunk?

100
00:07:59.338 --> 00:08:01.423
A little. Just enough to wake me up.

101
00:08:02.424 --> 00:08:03.425
Fancy car.

102
00:08:03.508 --> 00:08:06.511
Yeah. it's one of those new
EdenTech electric ones.

103
00:08:06.595 --> 00:08:08.055
Electric. huh?

104
00:08:08.138 --> 00:08:11.725
I remember when the only things
that were electric were eels. chairs.

105
00:08:12.225 --> 00:08:14.770
and Catherine Zeta-Jones in Chicago.

106
00:08:21.151 --> 00:08:22.653
Empty pill bottles.

107
00:08:38.710 --> 00:08:40.003
Who was he?

108
00:08:40.629 --> 00:08:43.131
Simon Davenport. 53 years old.

109
00:08:43.215 --> 00:08:44.883
No wife. no kids.

110
00:08:44.967 --> 00:08:46.635
He's got a sister out in Hancock Park.

111
00:08:46.718 --> 00:08:49.805
but we don't really know anything
about her other than her name.

112
00:08:49.888 --> 00:08:51.723
Beth Davenport.

113
00:08:51.807 --> 00:08:54.434
Divorced. 5'6". 130 pounds.

114
00:08:54.977 --> 00:08:58.230
Spitfire of a personality.
Self-proclaimed chocoholic.

115
00:08:58.313 --> 00:09:02.526
Likes outdoorsy things. but is just
as happy curling up with a good book.

116
00:09:03.151 --> 00:09:06.488
All right. I've seen enough.
Mark it as suicide.

117
00:09:07.489 --> 00:09:08.490
Go ahead!

118
00:09:08.573 --> 00:09:09.783
Bring in the crane!

119
00:09:35.892 --> 00:09:37.537
- Oh. my God. it's up!
- Wait. I got to see what I got!

120
00:09:37.561 --> 00:09:38.729
- Yes. I got it!
- Congrats.

121
00:09:38.812 --> 00:09:40.731
- Come on. man!
- She can't even sing!

122
00:09:46.570 --> 00:09:48.488
- Lieutenant?
- What's up. Barnes?

123
00:09:48.572 --> 00:09:51.426
Look. I know you're off the bank job.
sir. but I could really use your advice.

124
00:09:51.450 --> 00:09:53.369
- Go for it.
- Look. it's the strangest thing.

125
00:09:53.452 --> 00:09:55.287
All the thieves had never
met each other

126
00:09:55.370 --> 00:09:57.140
and none of them knew
who they were working for.

127
00:09:57.164 --> 00:09:58.165
Brilliant!

128
00:09:58.248 --> 00:10:01.001
If they don't know anything.
they can't squeal.

129
00:10:01.084 --> 00:10:03.211
Whoever orchestrated this
is very smart.

130
00:10:03.295 --> 00:10:06.631
And get this. The robbers were told
that they could keep the cash.

131
00:10:06.715 --> 00:10:09.760
Who organizes a bank robbery
and doesn't keep the cash?

132
00:10:09.843 --> 00:10:11.678
They must have been
after something else.

133
00:10:12.345 --> 00:10:13.823
Why don't you bring in
one of the perps?

134
00:10:13.847 --> 00:10:15.265
See if we can get them talking.

135
00:10:15.348 --> 00:10:16.433
Got it. Thank you.

136
00:10:17.601 --> 00:10:19.811
Heads up. Frank. You got a visitor.

137
00:10:20.353 --> 00:10:22.898
I told her to wait outside.
but she just walked in.

138
00:10:23.565 --> 00:10:24.816
You want me to get rid of her?

139
00:10:29.196 --> 00:10:30.405
No.

140
00:10:30.489 --> 00:10:31.948
That's okay. I'll deal with it.

141
00:10:42.084 --> 00:10:43.168
Over here. Lieutenant.

142
00:10:48.215 --> 00:10:50.550
I'd sworn off love after my wife died.

143
00:10:50.634 --> 00:10:53.512
but this woman was put together
in all the right ways.

144
00:10:53.595 --> 00:10:56.681
Face. head. shoulders. knees and toes.

145
00:10:56.765 --> 00:10:58.642
Knees and toes...

146
00:10:58.725 --> 00:11:02.062
and a bottom that would make
any toilet beg for the brown.

147
00:11:04.397 --> 00:11:05.982
Sorry to keep you waiting. ma'am.

148
00:11:07.609 --> 00:11:08.819
How may I help you?

149
00:11:08.902 --> 00:11:12.948
You're wrong about Simon Davenport.
He wouldn't commit suicide.

150
00:11:13.031 --> 00:11:14.491
Simon Davenport.

151
00:11:14.574 --> 00:11:16.409
The stiff from the Malibu crash.

152
00:11:16.493 --> 00:11:18.078
That stiff was my brother.

153
00:11:18.662 --> 00:11:21.081
I mean...
he wasn't that stiff. really.

154
00:11:21.164 --> 00:11:23.708
Not yet. More floppy and bloated.

155
00:11:24.251 --> 00:11:26.503
No. I mean.
I'm so sorry for your loss.

156
00:11:26.586 --> 00:11:27.879
Please. take a chair.

157
00:11:27.963 --> 00:11:30.924
No. thank you.
I have plenty of chairs at home.

158
00:11:33.009 --> 00:11:35.345
Now. Mrs...

159
00:11:35.428 --> 00:11:36.429
Davenport.

160
00:11:37.013 --> 00:11:39.141
Miss Beth Davenport.

161
00:11:39.641 --> 00:11:41.685
- Mr.?
- Drebin.

162
00:11:41.768 --> 00:11:42.769
Miss...

163
00:11:43.270 --> 00:11:45.647
Detective Frank Drebin.

164
00:11:45.730 --> 00:11:48.233
Detective. I think
someone murdered Simon.

165
00:11:48.316 --> 00:11:50.235
Really? What makes you think that?

166
00:11:50.318 --> 00:11:51.736
Well. he called me last night.

167
00:11:51.820 --> 00:11:53.423
He said he was
in some kind of trouble.

168
00:11:53.504 --> 00:11:55.323
So we made plans to meet this morning.

169
00:11:55.407 --> 00:11:58.076
Does that sound like someone
who's planning to kill themselves?

170
00:11:58.160 --> 00:12:00.287
No. it certainly does not.

171
00:12:00.829 --> 00:12:02.622
Why would someone do that to him?

172
00:12:05.333 --> 00:12:06.334
Trust me.

173
00:12:06.418 --> 00:12:08.753
there's always a reason
to kill someone.

174
00:12:08.837 --> 00:12:11.131
Did he have an obnoxious laugh?

175
00:12:11.214 --> 00:12:12.549
No.

176
00:12:12.632 --> 00:12:14.843
Forgive me. I'm just not myself.

177
00:12:14.926 --> 00:12:16.887
That's okay. I'm not you. either.

178
00:12:19.306 --> 00:12:20.348
Tell me.

179
00:12:20.432 --> 00:12:22.309
what did your brother do for work?

180
00:12:22.392 --> 00:12:23.476
Computers.

181
00:12:24.227 --> 00:12:25.979
He was a programmer for Richard Cane.

182
00:12:26.062 --> 00:12:29.149
The genius who's gonna save
the world with his electric cars.

183
00:12:29.232 --> 00:12:30.832
He's the first person
you should talk to.

184
00:12:30.901 --> 00:12:33.504
Then you could check Simon's
driving records and see if they match.

185
00:12:33.528 --> 00:12:34.613
Slow down there.

186
00:12:34.696 --> 00:12:35.697
Excuse me?

187
00:12:35.780 --> 00:12:37.991
Let's just leave the police work
to me. okay?

188
00:12:39.826 --> 00:12:40.911
I see.

189
00:12:40.994 --> 00:12:42.621
Same old story with guys like you.

190
00:12:42.704 --> 00:12:43.830
Guys like me?

191
00:12:43.914 --> 00:12:46.041
Stubborn old men
who think they know what's best.

192
00:12:49.419 --> 00:12:52.464
I understand you're upset.
but this is what I do.

193
00:12:52.547 --> 00:12:55.800
If someone did off your brother.
I'll find him.

194
00:12:55.884 --> 00:12:59.012
I appreciate that. Detective.
But Simon was all I had.

195
00:12:59.512 --> 00:13:02.474
So you'll forgive me if I don't just
sit around and hope you do your job.

196
00:13:02.557 --> 00:13:05.310
That's exactly
what I expect you to do.

197
00:13:05.393 --> 00:13:07.354
When I have something.
I'll contact you.

198
00:13:07.812 --> 00:13:10.148
I'm doing a series
of book readings this week.

199
00:13:10.232 --> 00:13:11.441
You can find me there.

200
00:13:12.400 --> 00:13:13.735
Book readings?

201
00:13:13.818 --> 00:13:16.894
Yes. I write true-crime novels based
on fictional stories that I make up.

202
00:13:18.365 --> 00:13:20.116
Yes. well.

203
00:13:20.200 --> 00:13:23.203
you may write about it. but I live it.

204
00:13:24.412 --> 00:13:27.958
Now. if you'll excuse me.
we're having a birthday party

205
00:13:28.041 --> 00:13:30.293
and I'm the best singer in the office.

206
00:13:35.173 --> 00:13:37.676
On second thought.
I will take that chair.

207
00:13:47.060 --> 00:13:50.230
I couldn't remember the last time
someone had talked to me like that.

208
00:13:50.730 --> 00:13:53.817
It was the kind of dressing down
you usually have to pay for

209
00:13:53.900 --> 00:13:55.735
in the basement of a laundromat.
But she...

210
00:13:55.819 --> 00:13:57.362
She had the kind of hips

211
00:13:57.445 --> 00:13:59.990
you wanted to put
a hula hoop on and spin.

212
00:14:00.073 --> 00:14:01.408
The kind that made you...

213
00:14:04.661 --> 00:14:06.037
Fellas. do you mind?

214
00:14:11.751 --> 00:14:15.005
I wasn't convinced Simon Davenport
had been murdered.

215
00:14:15.088 --> 00:14:17.590
But the case was starting
to give me an itch.

216
00:14:17.674 --> 00:14:19.342
And when I start to scratch.

217
00:14:19.426 --> 00:14:23.930
I don't stop till I break skin
and the doctor makes me wear mittens.

218
00:14:25.098 --> 00:14:26.099
Thanks.

219
00:14:36.318 --> 00:14:37.819
- Coat check?
- Champagne?

220
00:14:47.704 --> 00:14:50.665
Richard Cane had made
his first fortune in microprocessors.

221
00:14:51.249 --> 00:14:54.919
and then used it to build
a vast online retail marketplace

222
00:14:55.003 --> 00:14:57.088
and green technology empire.

223
00:15:01.051 --> 00:15:04.179
Then. suddenly.
the bear charges towards me.

224
00:15:04.262 --> 00:15:05.722
I ready my knife...

225
00:15:06.306 --> 00:15:10.268
and he barrels right past me
to a honey hive above the campsite!

226
00:15:11.269 --> 00:15:14.939
It had been there all along!
And I hadn't seen it.

227
00:15:22.572 --> 00:15:23.698
You've arrived.

228
00:15:25.116 --> 00:15:26.117
Lieutenant Drebin.

229
00:15:26.659 --> 00:15:27.702
- Me. too!
- I'm Richar...

230
00:15:28.203 --> 00:15:29.204
Richard Cane.

231
00:15:29.788 --> 00:15:31.331
Please. walk with me.

232
00:15:32.457 --> 00:15:35.543
So. what can you tell me
about Mr. Davenport?

233
00:15:35.627 --> 00:15:38.630
Simon was a brilliant engineer.
and one of our best.

234
00:15:39.297 --> 00:15:42.217
I had no idea
he was so terribly depressed.

235
00:15:42.300 --> 00:15:44.719
Suicide is a dreadful thing.

236
00:15:44.803 --> 00:15:46.262
Possible suicide.

237
00:15:46.346 --> 00:15:48.056
You suspect something foul?

238
00:15:48.139 --> 00:15:50.350
No. A chicken probably
couldn't do this.

239
00:15:50.433 --> 00:15:53.311
- But I'm not ruling anything out.
- I see.

240
00:15:53.395 --> 00:15:56.064
Was this one of the projects
Simon was working on?

241
00:15:56.147 --> 00:15:59.401
No. what you see here
is a red light therapy machine

242
00:15:59.484 --> 00:16:01.569
proven to increase testosterone.

243
00:16:01.653 --> 00:16:04.531
Did you know that men's
sperm count is at historic lows

244
00:16:04.614 --> 00:16:06.491
- across the board?
- Fascinating.

245
00:16:07.200 --> 00:16:09.577
I've never put my sperm
across a board.

246
00:16:09.661 --> 00:16:11.830
I have an old
Bon Jovi T-shirt for that.

247
00:16:15.667 --> 00:16:18.670
You know. I hope you don't think
it's awkward my saying this.

248
00:16:18.753 --> 00:16:21.423
but I'm actually a big fan of yours.

249
00:16:21.506 --> 00:16:22.674
- Is that so?
- Yes.

250
00:16:22.757 --> 00:16:24.926
I read about your work
at the bank robbery.

251
00:16:25.009 --> 00:16:27.262
Guys like you are a dying breed.

252
00:16:28.179 --> 00:16:31.015
- Guys like me?
- Yes. men of action

253
00:16:31.099 --> 00:16:34.102
who don't ask permission to fix
what they know is broken.

254
00:16:34.185 --> 00:16:36.271
I'm surprised to hear you say that.

255
00:16:36.354 --> 00:16:39.274
coming from someone
who's so into these gadgets.

256
00:16:40.608 --> 00:16:43.278
You don't enjoy the marvels
of the modern age?

257
00:16:44.195 --> 00:16:46.865
No offense.
but the world was better before.

258
00:16:46.948 --> 00:16:49.284
I agree. but don't tell anyone.

259
00:16:50.827 --> 00:16:51.870
Cigar?

260
00:16:51.953 --> 00:16:53.455
Looks it to me.

261
00:16:54.247 --> 00:16:55.748
No. would you like one?

262
00:16:56.499 --> 00:16:57.959
Smoking indoors?

263
00:16:58.042 --> 00:16:59.544
Care to write me a ticket?

264
00:17:04.299 --> 00:17:05.383
That matchbook.

265
00:17:06.092 --> 00:17:07.427
I've seen it before.

266
00:17:09.053 --> 00:17:10.221
It's the Bengal.

267
00:17:11.264 --> 00:17:13.850
It's a supper club I own
for some of the city's elite.

268
00:17:13.933 --> 00:17:16.769
It's the kind of place
where men can be themselves.

269
00:17:16.853 --> 00:17:18.021
have a few drinks and...

270
00:17:18.563 --> 00:17:21.900
like the Black Eyed Peas once said.
"get retarded in here."

271
00:17:22.901 --> 00:17:24.569
You can still say that word?

272
00:17:24.652 --> 00:17:26.446
In my club. you can.

273
00:17:26.529 --> 00:17:28.656
Well. I love the Black Eyed Peas.

274
00:17:28.740 --> 00:17:30.408
- Who doesn't?
- I know a few people.

275
00:17:30.492 --> 00:17:32.243
- They're fools.
- I know.

276
00:17:32.911 --> 00:17:34.787
- Will.i.am.
- Apl.de.ap.

277
00:17:34.871 --> 00:17:35.872
Taboo.

278
00:17:35.955 --> 00:17:38.791
- Don't forget Fergie.
- I would never forget Fergie.

279
00:17:38.875 --> 00:17:40.210
The Dutchess.

280
00:17:42.212 --> 00:17:44.005
Well. if you need anything.

281
00:17:44.088 --> 00:17:45.840
please don't hesitate to call.

282
00:17:46.674 --> 00:17:48.426
Thank you. I'll be in touch.

283
00:17:54.849 --> 00:17:57.101
- It's that way.
- Of course.

284
00:18:05.944 --> 00:18:10.281
Why don't we get Mr. Drebin
a little gift for tomorrow?

285
00:18:12.492 --> 00:18:14.285
The EdenVox-1.

286
00:18:14.369 --> 00:18:17.539
Police Squad's first ever
fully automated. self-driving

287
00:18:17.622 --> 00:18:19.332
electric vehicle.

288
00:18:19.415 --> 00:18:21.584
A gift we just received
from Richard Cane.

289
00:18:21.668 --> 00:18:24.420
You must've made some kind
of impression last night. Frank.

290
00:18:24.504 --> 00:18:25.922
Yeah. it would seem so.

291
00:18:26.005 --> 00:18:27.674
- Coffee?
- Yes. thank you.

292
00:18:27.757 --> 00:18:29.842
Don't be shy. fellas.
Come check it out.

293
00:18:33.471 --> 00:18:34.556
Snug.

294
00:18:34.639 --> 00:18:36.015
All electric.

295
00:18:36.099 --> 00:18:38.351
Zero to sixty in 3.1 seconds.

296
00:18:38.434 --> 00:18:40.270
I guess that's good.

297
00:18:40.353 --> 00:18:41.354
Watch this.

298
00:18:41.437 --> 00:18:43.773
Car. open doors.

299
00:18:46.109 --> 00:18:47.277
Neat trick.

300
00:18:47.360 --> 00:18:48.570
Now you try.

301
00:18:49.946 --> 00:18:50.947
Car...

302
00:18:51.531 --> 00:18:52.991
please. close doors.

303
00:18:57.161 --> 00:18:59.539
- Hey!
- Pretty fun. I guess.

304
00:18:59.622 --> 00:19:01.207
Okay. how about this? Car...

305
00:19:01.291 --> 00:19:03.668
drive forward 30 feet.

306
00:19:13.511 --> 00:19:15.555
- Pretty smooth.
- All right.

307
00:19:21.477 --> 00:19:22.478
Impressive.

308
00:19:22.562 --> 00:19:23.980
Hey! Guys?

309
00:19:24.063 --> 00:19:25.315
- Freeze!
- Don't...

310
00:19:25.398 --> 00:19:26.482
What?

311
00:19:27.817 --> 00:19:29.736
Stop! Don't move!

312
00:19:30.153 --> 00:19:32.739
I tell you.
this place is falling apart.

313
00:19:35.533 --> 00:19:38.328
I got half a dozen witnesses
that place you on the scene.

314
00:19:38.411 --> 00:19:40.538
We know you were at the bank!

315
00:19:40.622 --> 00:19:42.874
I'm telling you. I wasn't there.

316
00:19:45.960 --> 00:19:46.961
Thanks. Park.

317
00:19:49.047 --> 00:19:52.717
This is quite the rap sheet
you've got here.

318
00:19:53.217 --> 00:19:56.554
It says you served 20 years
for "man's laughter".

319
00:19:57.430 --> 00:19:59.015
Must have been quite the joke.

320
00:19:59.098 --> 00:20:00.308
You mean "manslaughter"?

321
00:20:03.728 --> 00:20:04.812
Well...

322
00:20:05.855 --> 00:20:07.857
we know your boss didn't want cash.

323
00:20:07.940 --> 00:20:10.777
So what was the point of the robbery?
What did he want?

324
00:20:11.319 --> 00:20:14.155
I... wasn't... there.

325
00:20:14.238 --> 00:20:15.865
You think you're so smart.

326
00:20:16.449 --> 00:20:20.453
Well. I think my bodycam
might tell a different story.

327
00:20:20.536 --> 00:20:21.537
Ed?

328
00:20:24.165 --> 00:20:26.918
Technology really is something.

329
00:20:27.418 --> 00:20:30.838
Police Squad is all about
"transparency" these days.

330
00:20:35.593 --> 00:20:38.346
Dispatch. this is Drebin. 10-7.

331
00:20:38.429 --> 00:20:39.722
Yeah!

332
00:20:39.806 --> 00:20:41.057
A chili dog.

333
00:20:45.103 --> 00:20:46.771
Breakfast of champions.

334
00:20:46.854 --> 00:20:47.980
And a little black coffee.

335
00:20:48.064 --> 00:20:50.316
Okay. you can fast-forward a bit.

336
00:20:53.111 --> 00:20:54.862
License and registration. please.

337
00:20:58.616 --> 00:20:59.992
This isn't mine.

338
00:21:00.076 --> 00:21:01.077
Excuse me.

339
00:21:01.953 --> 00:21:03.746
Oh. boy. Listen.

340
00:21:03.830 --> 00:21:05.123
you seem like a decent fella.

341
00:21:05.206 --> 00:21:07.623
I'm gonna let you off with a warning.
Have a great day. bye.

342
00:21:08.126 --> 00:21:10.837
It's much later in the day.
Fast-forward a while.

343
00:21:12.422 --> 00:21:14.090
You'll see. Just wait.

344
00:21:15.758 --> 00:21:18.136
I need a bathroom. Oh. God.

345
00:21:18.219 --> 00:21:19.971
Come on. move. move. move!

346
00:21:20.471 --> 00:21:22.181
Focus. Frank. focus.

347
00:21:22.849 --> 00:21:24.559
You got this. you got this.

348
00:21:28.980 --> 00:21:30.022
Maybe a little more.

349
00:21:30.106 --> 00:21:31.691
I'm gonna ruin another suit!

350
00:21:31.774 --> 00:21:32.859
Barnes!

351
00:21:33.651 --> 00:21:34.652
Sorry.

352
00:21:35.903 --> 00:21:36.946
Police business!

353
00:21:37.655 --> 00:21:39.240
There is a line. man!

354
00:21:43.995 --> 00:21:44.996
Come on!

355
00:21:49.208 --> 00:21:51.878
You're disgusting. you stupid idiot.

356
00:21:53.296 --> 00:21:56.048
Breastfed until you were 13.
you freak.

357
00:21:57.884 --> 00:22:01.387
Can't get it up without the stench
of milk on your chin.

358
00:22:02.722 --> 00:22:03.723
Don't you dare.

359
00:22:04.307 --> 00:22:06.184
Don't do it. Don't eat it!

360
00:22:07.226 --> 00:22:09.270
- Oh. God!
- Frank.

361
00:22:09.353 --> 00:22:11.314
I had five more that day.

362
00:22:11.397 --> 00:22:13.441
- Feel better. Frank?
- You better believe it.

363
00:22:20.031 --> 00:22:21.032
Yes!

364
00:22:21.532 --> 00:22:24.368
That's you inside the bank.
plain as day.

365
00:22:24.452 --> 00:22:25.453
Okay. fine.

366
00:22:25.536 --> 00:22:27.830
Whoever we was working for.
they was crazy.

367
00:22:28.623 --> 00:22:31.459
I mean. they just wanted us to get
some safe deposit box.

368
00:22:31.542 --> 00:22:32.877
Safe deposit box.

369
00:22:40.968 --> 00:22:43.429
There. Box 595.

370
00:22:43.513 --> 00:22:45.640
- Ed. check the list.
- Yep.

371
00:22:47.683 --> 00:22:50.144
You're not gonna
believe this one. Frank.

372
00:22:50.228 --> 00:22:52.271
Simon Davenport.

373
00:22:52.355 --> 00:22:53.856
So you're saying.

374
00:22:54.732 --> 00:22:56.067
these two cases...

375
00:22:57.151 --> 00:22:58.319
are one case.

376
00:23:00.404 --> 00:23:03.574
Gentlemen. when you joined me
to launch EdenTech.

377
00:23:03.658 --> 00:23:04.826
it was with one goal.

378
00:23:05.493 --> 00:23:06.661
To save the world.

379
00:23:06.744 --> 00:23:09.872
Together. we've created technologies
to rival the Gods.

380
00:23:09.956 --> 00:23:11.582
Has the world gotten any better?

381
00:23:11.666 --> 00:23:14.585
No. It's only gotten worse.

382
00:23:15.086 --> 00:23:17.630
Now. when the Founding Fathers
created this country.

383
00:23:18.089 --> 00:23:21.843
they sat in a room like this.
filled with men like us.

384
00:23:22.426 --> 00:23:24.470
and birthed an empire.

385
00:23:24.554 --> 00:23:26.055
The USA.

386
00:23:26.973 --> 00:23:27.974
Yes. that's right.

387
00:23:28.558 --> 00:23:29.725
But as years went by.

388
00:23:30.226 --> 00:23:32.687
other people wanted
to get into that room.

389
00:23:32.770 --> 00:23:33.771
Fish people.

390
00:23:33.855 --> 00:23:34.856
- What?
- Fish people.

391
00:23:35.314 --> 00:23:36.899
Gills on their necks.

392
00:23:36.983 --> 00:23:39.902
- I don't...
- Like mermen and merwomen.

393
00:23:39.986 --> 00:23:41.612
- Mermaids.
- Right.

394
00:23:41.696 --> 00:23:43.531
No. stop. Not fish people.

395
00:23:43.614 --> 00:23:45.157
Ungrateful people.

396
00:23:45.241 --> 00:23:48.953
People that did not earn their seat
at the table.

397
00:23:49.537 --> 00:23:52.582
People not built
like the men in this room.

398
00:23:52.665 --> 00:23:53.666
Crab hands.

399
00:23:53.749 --> 00:23:56.794
They had crab hands
instead of fingers.

400
00:23:56.878 --> 00:23:59.797
Stop! I know what I mean.
So just let me do the talking.

401
00:23:59.881 --> 00:24:02.300
- This is a crab-hand person.
- I've met him.

402
00:24:02.383 --> 00:24:03.467
Put the phone away!

403
00:24:06.387 --> 00:24:09.098
Now. it is time for us to admit

404
00:24:09.181 --> 00:24:11.309
that the path we are on
is not working.

405
00:24:11.392 --> 00:24:13.144
The system's broken.

406
00:24:13.227 --> 00:24:15.813
And what does one do
when a system is malfunctioning?

407
00:24:16.314 --> 00:24:17.440
You unplug it.

408
00:24:18.274 --> 00:24:19.275
And then...

409
00:24:20.359 --> 00:24:21.652
you plug it in again.

410
00:24:21.736 --> 00:24:26.157
I call it the Primordial
Law of Toughness Device.

411
00:24:26.240 --> 00:24:28.242
Now let me show you
what it's capable of.

412
00:24:28.743 --> 00:24:32.204
Last year. we set up cameras
at the local community center.

413
00:24:32.288 --> 00:24:34.582
Decided to run a little experiment.

414
00:24:34.665 --> 00:24:35.791
The question.

415
00:24:35.875 --> 00:24:37.460
What would happen to modern humans

416
00:24:37.543 --> 00:24:41.005
if you reverted their psyche
to an original state of nature?

417
00:24:45.134 --> 00:24:48.554
When activated.
the device sends an audio frequency

418
00:24:48.638 --> 00:24:51.849
that reduces the brain
to its animalistic core.

419
00:24:52.808 --> 00:24:54.769
In this case.
the frequency was limited.

420
00:24:54.852 --> 00:24:59.106
But next time. it will spread
through every smart device

421
00:24:59.190 --> 00:25:01.525
until the entire world is infected.

422
00:25:01.609 --> 00:25:03.194
As for us. upon detonation.

423
00:25:03.277 --> 00:25:07.114
we will decamp to one
of my super bunkers around the world

424
00:25:07.198 --> 00:25:09.283
where there will be food and water.

425
00:25:09.367 --> 00:25:12.203
and the best live entertainment
the world has to offer.

426
00:25:12.286 --> 00:25:13.788
What's up. evil billionaires?

427
00:25:13.871 --> 00:25:16.666
I am so excited to be doing live shows

428
00:25:16.749 --> 00:25:20.252
for as long as it takes.
in the Doomsday Giggle Bunkeroom

429
00:25:20.336 --> 00:25:22.755
located in Block 4
of the Arizona District.

430
00:25:23.381 --> 00:25:24.632
See you there!

431
00:25:24.715 --> 00:25:25.758
Amish Paradise.

432
00:25:27.093 --> 00:25:28.970
And when the embers have died down.

433
00:25:29.053 --> 00:25:31.931
any survivors left will have earned
their place alongside us.

434
00:25:32.014 --> 00:25:34.266
and we will return to a world

435
00:25:34.350 --> 00:25:37.228
that is but a blank slate
upon which we can rebuild

436
00:25:37.311 --> 00:25:40.314
as the founding fathers of a new Eden.

437
00:25:40.398 --> 00:25:42.149
Gentlemen. lady.

438
00:25:42.692 --> 00:25:44.402
this New Year's Eve. I give you...

439
00:25:45.528 --> 00:25:46.862
Project Inferno!

440
00:26:00.209 --> 00:26:02.795
It turned out that Cane's nightclub
was only half a mile

441
00:26:02.878 --> 00:26:04.588
from where Simon Davenport crashed.

442
00:26:05.172 --> 00:26:06.507
And that got me thinking.

443
00:26:06.590 --> 00:26:08.759
Maybe he had been there
the night he died.

444
00:26:08.843 --> 00:26:11.095
So I hopped
into my new electric cruiser

445
00:26:11.178 --> 00:26:13.097
and told it to head to Malibu.

446
00:26:13.180 --> 00:26:14.682
Warning. Please take the wheel.

447
00:26:14.765 --> 00:26:17.101
Warning. Please take the wheel.

448
00:26:17.184 --> 00:26:18.728
Warning. Please take the wheel.

449
00:26:18.811 --> 00:26:21.772
Collision detected.
Please take the wheel.

450
00:26:21.856 --> 00:26:23.315
Get out of the road! Move!

451
00:26:23.983 --> 00:26:26.318
- What's wrong with you people?
- Collision detected.

452
00:26:26.402 --> 00:26:28.320
What is this city coming to?

453
00:26:48.758 --> 00:26:50.092
What can I get you?

454
00:26:50.801 --> 00:26:52.428
I was wondering if you could help me.

455
00:26:53.471 --> 00:26:56.640
I'm looking for a friend
who may have been here before.

456
00:26:57.349 --> 00:26:59.018
Nah. I haven't seen him.

457
00:26:59.101 --> 00:27:01.520
- You hardly looked at it.
- I saw enough.

458
00:27:04.273 --> 00:27:05.649
You don't remember me. do you?

459
00:27:06.358 --> 00:27:07.359
Should I?

460
00:27:07.443 --> 00:27:10.863
My brother. you shot him
"in the name of justice."

461
00:27:10.946 --> 00:27:12.782
That can literally be
thousands of people.

462
00:27:12.865 --> 00:27:14.301
Shot him in the back as he ran away.

463
00:27:14.325 --> 00:27:15.576
- Hundreds.
- Unarmed.

464
00:27:15.659 --> 00:27:16.994
- At least 50.
- He was white.

465
00:27:17.912 --> 00:27:19.872
So you're Tony Roiland's brother!

466
00:27:19.955 --> 00:27:20.956
That's right.

467
00:27:21.040 --> 00:27:23.209
- How is old Tony?
- Are you serious?

468
00:27:23.292 --> 00:27:24.376
Bad.

469
00:27:25.711 --> 00:27:26.712
Right.

470
00:27:27.338 --> 00:27:30.257
So. your friend. maybe I have
seen him. Maybe I haven't.

471
00:27:31.300 --> 00:27:32.551
I can't remember.

472
00:27:32.635 --> 00:27:35.096
- You can't remember. huh?
- Nah.

473
00:27:35.179 --> 00:27:37.139
Well. maybe this'll jog your memory.

474
00:27:45.022 --> 00:27:46.774
That's better. Remember now?

475
00:27:46.857 --> 00:27:47.858
Yeah. I remember.

476
00:27:47.942 --> 00:27:50.194
He sat in a corner booth.
He had a drink.

477
00:27:50.277 --> 00:27:51.445
But that's all I know.

478
00:27:51.529 --> 00:27:53.197
Where do they keep
surveillance footage?

479
00:27:54.031 --> 00:27:55.074
In the back.

480
00:27:55.741 --> 00:27:57.827
But even I'm not allowed in there.

481
00:28:04.250 --> 00:28:05.251
Thank you.

482
00:28:07.920 --> 00:28:10.089
And there she was again.

483
00:28:10.172 --> 00:28:12.716
I had to admit. she was beautiful.

484
00:28:12.800 --> 00:28:14.927
She had a body
that carried her head around.

485
00:28:15.010 --> 00:28:16.762
and a butt that seemed to say.

486
00:28:16.846 --> 00:28:18.931
"Hello. I'm a talking butt."

487
00:28:19.890 --> 00:28:22.143
Elegant? Yeah. I'd say so.

488
00:28:23.185 --> 00:28:25.688
But like a teenager
with three babysitting jobs.

489
00:28:25.771 --> 00:28:28.149
I didn't need another babysitting job.

490
00:28:28.232 --> 00:28:29.817
Hello. Lieutenant.

491
00:28:29.900 --> 00:28:31.443
What the hell are you doing here?

492
00:28:31.527 --> 00:28:33.112
I'm doing the same thing you are.

493
00:28:33.195 --> 00:28:35.447
I told you
I wasn't gonna sit around and wait.

494
00:28:35.531 --> 00:28:37.867
Listen. this isn't
one of your stories.

495
00:28:37.950 --> 00:28:41.829
Average civilian women
don't suddenly solve crimes.

496
00:28:41.912 --> 00:28:43.205
You read my book.

497
00:28:43.914 --> 00:28:44.915
What'd you think?

498
00:28:45.374 --> 00:28:46.709
I think it's a fantasy.

499
00:28:47.209 --> 00:28:51.255
A woman puts on a wig and sunglasses
and suddenly she's an assassin?

500
00:28:51.338 --> 00:28:52.715
But did you enjoy it?

501
00:28:53.591 --> 00:28:55.050
It had some good parts.

502
00:28:57.261 --> 00:28:58.596
Lieutenant Drebin.

503
00:28:58.679 --> 00:29:00.514
Does he know you're Simon's sister?

504
00:29:01.223 --> 00:29:03.559
- No.
- Good. Let's keep it that way.

505
00:29:03.642 --> 00:29:05.060
What a wonderful surprise.

506
00:29:05.144 --> 00:29:06.562
Fine. thank you.

507
00:29:06.979 --> 00:29:08.939
Beautiful place you've got here.

508
00:29:09.023 --> 00:29:10.649
Can't smell the dead animals at all.

509
00:29:10.733 --> 00:29:11.734
Thank you.

510
00:29:12.693 --> 00:29:13.986
Can I get you a drink?

511
00:29:14.069 --> 00:29:15.863
Just water. And sparkling.

512
00:29:20.034 --> 00:29:22.620
And who is this stunning creature?

513
00:29:23.120 --> 00:29:24.663
I don't believe we've met.

514
00:29:24.747 --> 00:29:27.541
- Well. I'm...
- This is Miss...

515
00:29:28.042 --> 00:29:29.043
Cherry...

516
00:29:30.169 --> 00:29:31.337
Roosevelt...

517
00:29:32.129 --> 00:29:34.340
Fat Bozo Chowing Spaghetti.

518
00:29:35.007 --> 00:29:36.800
- What an interesting name.
- Yes.

519
00:29:37.343 --> 00:29:38.344
Thank you.

520
00:29:38.427 --> 00:29:40.596
So. Lieutenant. what brings you here?

521
00:29:40.679 --> 00:29:44.099
I was hoping you could let me
take a look at your security footage.

522
00:29:44.767 --> 00:29:45.893
May I ask why?

523
00:29:45.976 --> 00:29:47.269
Go right ahead.

524
00:29:52.733 --> 00:29:54.860
Unfortunately. I can't show you
security footage.

525
00:29:54.944 --> 00:29:57.112
Our members trust
that we will provide them

526
00:29:57.196 --> 00:29:58.989
with the highest level of privacy.

527
00:29:59.573 --> 00:30:00.991
I hope you understand.

528
00:30:01.075 --> 00:30:02.159
I'm starting to.

529
00:30:03.244 --> 00:30:04.954
Well. thank you so much for the drink.

530
00:30:05.037 --> 00:30:07.248
It's getting late.
We really must be going.

531
00:30:07.331 --> 00:30:08.332
So soon?

532
00:30:08.415 --> 00:30:10.459
I hope you're not leaving. too.
Miss Spaghetti.

533
00:30:10.918 --> 00:30:13.337
- Well. I...
- Yes. she's leaving. too.

534
00:30:13.420 --> 00:30:15.673
Early morning at Disneyland tomorrow.

535
00:30:15.756 --> 00:30:17.299
She's one of those Disney adults.

536
00:30:17.383 --> 00:30:20.678
Obsessed. really.
Her bed is covered in dolls.

537
00:30:21.887 --> 00:30:23.764
Miss Spaghetti.
please stay for a drink.

538
00:30:24.723 --> 00:30:26.725
You don't mind. do you. Drebin?

539
00:30:26.809 --> 00:30:27.893
Be my guest.

540
00:30:27.977 --> 00:30:29.561
Wonderful. I'll get a table.

541
00:30:29.645 --> 00:30:30.646
Okay.

542
00:30:32.273 --> 00:30:34.692
You get the footage.
I'll keep him occupied.

543
00:30:34.775 --> 00:30:36.277
Absolutely not!

544
00:30:43.951 --> 00:30:45.160
Thank you.

545
00:30:46.704 --> 00:30:48.747
Wow. This place is amazing.

546
00:30:49.498 --> 00:30:50.499
Thank you.

547
00:30:50.958 --> 00:30:53.210
Miss Spaghetti. may I speak freely?

548
00:30:53.294 --> 00:30:54.503
I'd prefer English.

549
00:30:55.254 --> 00:30:58.424
You're much too sophisticated
for the likes of Frank Drebin.

550
00:30:59.008 --> 00:31:00.718
I'm not with Drebin.

551
00:31:00.801 --> 00:31:02.803
Well. that's wonderful news!

552
00:31:11.603 --> 00:31:12.604
Cheers.

553
00:31:13.439 --> 00:31:14.898
From Bill Cosby's private estate.

554
00:31:56.899 --> 00:31:58.275
That hurt!

555
00:31:59.234 --> 00:32:00.402
Shoot!

556
00:32:02.029 --> 00:32:04.323
Mom. Mom. now is not a good time.

557
00:32:04.823 --> 00:32:07.076
Mom. please. I'll call you back.

558
00:32:07.159 --> 00:32:09.745
I got to go. I got to go.
I got to go now.

559
00:32:11.872 --> 00:32:13.207
So. tell me.

560
00:32:13.665 --> 00:32:15.501
what have you been working on lately?

561
00:32:15.584 --> 00:32:18.379
Let's not talk about work.
Let's talk about play.

562
00:32:21.090 --> 00:32:22.966
Do you like jazz. Miss Spaghetti?

563
00:32:23.050 --> 00:32:24.051
Like it?

564
00:32:24.802 --> 00:32:26.637
- I love it.
- I love it.

565
00:32:29.556 --> 00:32:30.724
Sir.

566
00:32:32.142 --> 00:32:33.143
We've got a problem.

567
00:32:33.227 --> 00:32:35.521
- Not now. Not now.
- No. it's quite...

568
00:32:36.730 --> 00:32:37.731
Yes. sir.

569
00:32:40.025 --> 00:32:41.944
This one's for my electric new friend.

570
00:32:42.778 --> 00:32:44.113
Richard Cane.

571
00:32:44.196 --> 00:32:45.280
Wow!

572
00:32:46.031 --> 00:32:47.866
Sassafras Chicken in D.

573
00:32:47.950 --> 00:32:49.868
Make it extra lumpy. boys.

574
00:33:04.466 --> 00:33:07.719
I've always said fighting
is a lot like jazz music.

575
00:33:07.803 --> 00:33:09.221
A scat-like improv

576
00:33:09.304 --> 00:33:12.641
where one lets imagination
take control of their body.

577
00:33:30.033 --> 00:33:31.034
I'm fine.

578
00:33:51.096 --> 00:33:52.181
Yeah!

579
00:34:06.445 --> 00:34:09.573
There's two things I love.
My stay-at-home girlfriend

580
00:34:09.656 --> 00:34:11.033
- and Gorilla Nut...
- Come on.

581
00:34:11.116 --> 00:34:12.868
...enhanced drink supplement for men.

582
00:34:13.243 --> 00:34:15.454
Don't follow fad diets
and fake workouts.

583
00:34:15.537 --> 00:34:17.873
You want to get ripped?
All you need is Muscle Slime.

584
00:34:17.956 --> 00:34:18.957
Rub it on and...

585
00:34:25.047 --> 00:34:26.882
Well. look at that.

586
00:34:32.054 --> 00:34:34.765
And who are you.
my secret eavesdropping friend?

587
00:34:38.352 --> 00:34:40.854
"Douglas O'Reilly.
investigative journalist.

588
00:34:40.938 --> 00:34:42.439
"L.A. Chronicle."

589
00:34:44.525 --> 00:34:45.609
Shoot.

590
00:35:01.166 --> 00:35:04.086
It seems Mr. Drebin might be
more of a problem than we thought.

591
00:35:04.169 --> 00:35:05.754
I want you to keep an eye on him.

592
00:35:05.837 --> 00:35:08.507
And make sure he doesn't cause
any more distractions.

593
00:35:08.590 --> 00:35:09.591
Yes. sir.

594
00:35:20.852 --> 00:35:22.604
Davis. This better be good.

595
00:35:23.772 --> 00:35:25.023
He did what?

596
00:35:25.649 --> 00:35:27.776
Get me Drebin this instant!

597
00:35:27.859 --> 00:35:30.487
Ma'am. I'm so sorry.
but you have to listen to me.

598
00:35:30.571 --> 00:35:32.155
There's something deeper
going on here.

599
00:35:33.323 --> 00:35:35.409
You wake up my husband.
I swear to God...

600
00:35:35.492 --> 00:35:36.493
I'm sorry.

601
00:35:36.577 --> 00:35:38.245
What the hell
were you thinking. Drebin?

602
00:35:38.328 --> 00:35:40.289
Richard Cane is a very powerful man.

603
00:35:40.372 --> 00:35:42.749
And he makes a lot of hefty
donations to this city.

604
00:35:42.833 --> 00:35:44.710
including the new car you're driving.

605
00:35:44.793 --> 00:35:46.003
Richard Cane is dirty.

606
00:35:46.086 --> 00:35:48.505
He's involved
with the Simon Davenport murder.

607
00:35:48.589 --> 00:35:50.549
And by the way. the bank job. too!

608
00:35:50.632 --> 00:35:52.092
You're still working the bank job?

609
00:35:52.843 --> 00:35:54.595
That's it. You're suspended!

610
00:35:54.678 --> 00:35:55.762
Suspended?

611
00:35:56.888 --> 00:35:58.724
What did I say about waking Ronald?

612
00:35:58.807 --> 00:36:01.310
He has a Fitzgerald
presentation tomorrow.

613
00:36:01.393 --> 00:36:06.440
And if Morimoto doesn't accept
his vertical-integration pitch.

614
00:36:06.523 --> 00:36:10.277
Bill Cantor will leapfrog him
for the third year in a row.

615
00:36:10.360 --> 00:36:12.362
- But Ronald trained Bill.
- Exactly!

616
00:36:12.446 --> 00:36:13.989
I've got no choice.

617
00:36:14.072 --> 00:36:17.159
I'm putting you on ice. Two weeks.
Effective immediately.

618
00:36:17.242 --> 00:36:18.243
Now get out.

619
00:36:19.953 --> 00:36:22.247
We're all rooting for you. Ronald.

620
00:36:22.331 --> 00:36:23.749
Give 'em hell tomorrow.

621
00:36:38.305 --> 00:36:39.348
Rough night?

622
00:36:41.016 --> 00:36:42.017
It's you.

623
00:36:42.601 --> 00:36:45.187
Now tell me. What'd you see
on the security footage?

624
00:36:45.270 --> 00:36:47.356
Listen. I feel for you. I really do.

625
00:36:47.439 --> 00:36:49.775
But I had to beat up
a lot of henchmen tonight.

626
00:36:49.858 --> 00:36:50.942
Men with daughters!

627
00:36:51.026 --> 00:36:53.654
Come on. You wouldn't even have
seen it if I didn't help you.

628
00:36:53.737 --> 00:36:55.155
Help me? That's rich.

629
00:36:55.238 --> 00:36:58.575
Now. if you'll excuse me.
I'm tired. I'm hungry.

630
00:36:59.284 --> 00:37:00.619
Goodnight. Miss Davenport.

631
00:37:04.748 --> 00:37:07.000
What if we had
a little dinner. together?

632
00:37:07.084 --> 00:37:08.669
I sure could go for a...

633
00:37:09.169 --> 00:37:10.170
bite.

634
00:37:10.253 --> 00:37:13.840
Slow down. chef.
This turkey burns at 450.

635
00:37:13.924 --> 00:37:16.510
- How hot was I cooking?
- About a thousand.

636
00:37:16.593 --> 00:37:18.845
Turkey needs slow and low.

637
00:37:18.929 --> 00:37:20.764
Unless you like your center pink.

638
00:37:21.765 --> 00:37:23.433
I love my centers pink.

639
00:37:23.517 --> 00:37:26.687
You're not worried the rare meat
will ruin a good stuffing?

640
00:37:26.770 --> 00:37:29.189
As long as you don't mind
if I get salmonella.

641
00:37:29.272 --> 00:37:31.274
Mind it? I prefer it.

642
00:37:31.775 --> 00:37:33.527
I like a sick little boy.

643
00:37:35.362 --> 00:37:37.489
You're not gonna stop hounding me.
are you?

644
00:37:38.156 --> 00:37:39.408
Not for a second.

645
00:38:01.555 --> 00:38:02.556
Thank you.

646
00:38:10.480 --> 00:38:11.732
Excuse the mess.

647
00:38:12.065 --> 00:38:13.066
I...

648
00:38:13.650 --> 00:38:15.652
haven't had the heart to clean

649
00:38:15.736 --> 00:38:17.195
since my wife died.

650
00:38:21.241 --> 00:38:23.910
My condolences. How did she pass?

651
00:38:23.994 --> 00:38:27.330
Great. Fifty yards easy.
Arm like a cannon.

652
00:38:28.248 --> 00:38:29.624
And then she died.

653
00:38:30.459 --> 00:38:32.836
So we'll never know
if she could've gone pro.

654
00:38:32.919 --> 00:38:35.338
She was the sweetest woman
I've ever known.

655
00:38:35.422 --> 00:38:39.176
- She sounds like a saint.
- Or maybe a Bronco or a 49er.

656
00:38:39.718 --> 00:38:41.720
We would've been happy
with any team. really.

657
00:38:42.262 --> 00:38:43.847
Anyone but the Browns.

658
00:38:49.561 --> 00:38:51.146
That's quite a view you have.

659
00:38:51.229 --> 00:38:54.399
You know. I've been drawn to the hills
ever since I moved here for college.

660
00:38:54.483 --> 00:38:55.525
UCLA?

661
00:38:56.151 --> 00:38:58.820
I see it every day. I live here.

662
00:38:58.904 --> 00:39:01.448
I'm afraid I don't have much to offer.

663
00:39:04.409 --> 00:39:05.410
However...

664
00:39:06.661 --> 00:39:10.332
All that turkey talk outside
got me in the Thanksgiving mood.

665
00:39:11.249 --> 00:39:14.336
I think I have a full turkey
around here somewhere.

666
00:39:14.419 --> 00:39:16.338
But my oven is filthy.

667
00:39:16.421 --> 00:39:19.299
I don't mind. I like a dirty bird.

668
00:39:43.156 --> 00:39:45.909
You weren't lying.
This oven is disgusting!

669
00:39:45.992 --> 00:39:49.162
It sure was fun to talk
about a dirty bird. but...

670
00:39:49.246 --> 00:39:50.831
it would be unsanitary.

671
00:40:00.674 --> 00:40:02.801
Well. hot brine
is the most important part.

672
00:40:02.884 --> 00:40:04.135
It sure is.

673
00:40:05.846 --> 00:40:06.847
This is my Buster.

674
00:40:07.222 --> 00:40:09.474
He must've smelled what's going on.

675
00:40:18.525 --> 00:40:20.986
Silly dog. that's not for you.

676
00:40:25.407 --> 00:40:26.408
Okay.

677
00:40:31.413 --> 00:40:32.873
He's so strong.

678
00:40:32.956 --> 00:40:34.332
Put that down.

679
00:40:35.917 --> 00:40:38.503
How about some nice scratches instead?

680
00:40:40.213 --> 00:40:41.214
Yes.

681
00:40:44.259 --> 00:40:45.427
Wow.

682
00:40:46.428 --> 00:40:48.513
I don't like this.

683
00:40:52.309 --> 00:40:54.477
Your hair. May I?

684
00:40:54.561 --> 00:40:55.979
Yes.

685
00:41:04.279 --> 00:41:05.447
That's better.

686
00:41:06.072 --> 00:41:07.198
Is this crazy?

687
00:41:07.741 --> 00:41:08.950
It's been a long time.

688
00:41:09.534 --> 00:41:12.245
I'm afraid I may have forgotten
how to kiss.

689
00:41:33.934 --> 00:41:35.101
How beautiful.

690
00:44:30.527 --> 00:44:33.029
After a relaxing weekend away
with Beth...

691
00:44:33.488 --> 00:44:34.489
Not again!

692
00:44:34.572 --> 00:44:36.574
...It was time to get back
to the case.

693
00:44:36.658 --> 00:44:38.701
So I called the L.A. Chronicle
news desk

694
00:44:38.785 --> 00:44:40.829
to follow up on Douglas O'Reilly.

695
00:44:40.912 --> 00:44:43.414
but was informed
that he hadn't made it into work.

696
00:44:43.498 --> 00:44:45.166
So I headed to his apartment.

697
00:44:47.001 --> 00:44:48.670
Douglas O'Reilly?

698
00:44:49.254 --> 00:44:51.923
Lieutenant Frank Drebin here.
Police Squad.

699
00:44:59.597 --> 00:45:00.849
Hello?

700
00:45:03.852 --> 00:45:05.186
Anyone home?

701
00:45:08.356 --> 00:45:09.858
Oh. no.

702
00:45:10.650 --> 00:45:14.070
Hey. Douglas.
I stepped in some kind of red liquid!

703
00:45:14.154 --> 00:45:15.864
You got any paper towels?

704
00:45:17.407 --> 00:45:19.409
I'm dragging it all over your place.

705
00:45:25.331 --> 00:45:27.834
I picked up your knife for you!

706
00:45:27.917 --> 00:45:29.335
Where do you want it?

707
00:45:31.963 --> 00:45:34.632
"Press record.
say your name and say. 'I did it."

708
00:45:39.470 --> 00:45:42.599
Lieutenant Frank Drebin. I did it.

709
00:45:44.225 --> 00:45:45.226
Okay.

710
00:45:48.146 --> 00:45:49.939
O'Reilly. that you?

711
00:45:59.574 --> 00:46:00.700
O'Reilly?

712
00:46:11.336 --> 00:46:12.837
And that's when it hit me.

713
00:46:12.921 --> 00:46:15.381
Like an idiot's finished
jigsaw puzzle.

714
00:46:15.465 --> 00:46:16.925
I was being framed.

715
00:46:17.884 --> 00:46:21.346
I needed to clean the crime scene.
No body. no crime.

716
00:46:24.557 --> 00:46:26.564
Hiding the body
was no longer an option.

717
00:46:26.645 --> 00:46:27.855
Freeze!

718
00:46:27.936 --> 00:46:29.270
It's not what it looks like!

719
00:46:35.818 --> 00:46:36.819
He's running!

720
00:46:40.406 --> 00:46:41.449
Car. drive.

721
00:46:46.287 --> 00:46:47.372
Thank you. car.

722
00:46:49.582 --> 00:46:50.583
What the...

723
00:46:53.628 --> 00:46:54.963
Car. stop it.

724
00:46:55.546 --> 00:46:56.631
I said stop!

725
00:46:56.714 --> 00:46:59.133
Hello. Drebin.
Mind if I take the wheel?

726
00:46:59.217 --> 00:47:00.927
Cane. What's going on?

727
00:47:01.010 --> 00:47:02.762
I've taken control of the car.

728
00:47:02.845 --> 00:47:05.765
It's a little trick I have
for when I want to fix mistakes.

729
00:47:05.848 --> 00:47:07.558
So that's how Davenport died.

730
00:47:07.642 --> 00:47:09.769
He didn't drive himself off a cliff.
you did.

731
00:47:09.852 --> 00:47:11.437
Now you're
getting somewhere. Detective.

732
00:47:11.521 --> 00:47:14.065
But not before he spilled your secrets
to that reporter.

733
00:47:14.148 --> 00:47:15.483
So you went and killed him. too.

734
00:47:15.566 --> 00:47:17.652
I didn't kill him. Frank. You did.

735
00:47:17.735 --> 00:47:19.612
You're the crazy cop
who stabbed the reporter

736
00:47:19.696 --> 00:47:21.406
and then drove himself into the ocean.

737
00:47:21.489 --> 00:47:22.865
The hell I am.

738
00:47:23.866 --> 00:47:25.412
There's no escape. Drebin.

739
00:47:25.493 --> 00:47:27.704
I'm just a little sad
that you won't be there

740
00:47:27.787 --> 00:47:30.320
to see what I have in store
when the New Year's Eve balls drop.

741
00:47:30.401 --> 00:47:32.166
Oh. well. Have a nice trip.

742
00:47:37.213 --> 00:47:38.589
Hi. Susan.

743
00:48:04.490 --> 00:48:06.784
Move! Move. move!

744
00:48:13.082 --> 00:48:15.293
Bees? No. No. No!

745
00:48:23.801 --> 00:48:25.720
Move! Out of the way! Move!

746
00:48:39.317 --> 00:48:40.860
It looks like you could use some help.

747
00:48:40.943 --> 00:48:42.820
What? Open the doors!

748
00:48:42.904 --> 00:48:44.280
You got it!

749
00:48:51.913 --> 00:48:54.165
Frank! Are you okay? Where are you?

750
00:48:54.248 --> 00:48:56.793
Never mind that.
I know how Simon Davenport was killed.

751
00:48:56.876 --> 00:48:59.045
It was Richard Cane.
He drove him off the cliff.

752
00:48:59.128 --> 00:49:01.214
Well. there's a warrant out
for your arrest.

753
00:49:01.297 --> 00:49:04.133
They're claiming that you killed
a reporter. Say it isn't so.

754
00:49:04.217 --> 00:49:05.259
It ain't so. Ed.

755
00:49:05.343 --> 00:49:08.429
There's another thing. Frank.
The mayor got wind of this whole mess

756
00:49:08.513 --> 00:49:10.473
- and they're pulling our funding.
- What?

757
00:49:10.556 --> 00:49:12.725
Police Squad is shut down
effective immediately.

758
00:49:12.809 --> 00:49:15.269
This is all because of me.
I'll fix this.

759
00:49:15.353 --> 00:49:17.271
- Do me a favor. Frank. Lay low.
- You got it.

760
00:49:17.355 --> 00:49:18.356
Thank you. Ed.

761
00:49:26.989 --> 00:49:28.907
Excuse me. do you have a phone
I could use?

762
00:49:29.617 --> 00:49:30.701
Thanks.

763
00:49:32.203 --> 00:49:35.373
As soon as I could.
I called Beth to break her the news.

764
00:49:35.456 --> 00:49:38.960
It wasn't easy. but I hoped
it would bring her some peace.

765
00:49:40.503 --> 00:49:41.504
Thanks.

766
00:49:42.088 --> 00:49:43.673
What the hell. man?

767
00:49:50.596 --> 00:49:51.597
Frank.

768
00:49:52.557 --> 00:49:53.683
Thank you.

769
00:49:54.725 --> 00:49:56.727
- God. you're hurt.
- It's nothing.

770
00:49:57.311 --> 00:49:58.646
Don't be silly. Come in.

771
00:50:04.068 --> 00:50:05.278
This is all I could find.

772
00:50:06.988 --> 00:50:08.030
Might sting a bit.

773
00:50:08.698 --> 00:50:09.699
Go for it.

774
00:50:12.535 --> 00:50:14.412
- It's okay. Keep going.
- Okay.

775
00:50:15.079 --> 00:50:18.583
Cane said he had something big
in store tomorrow for New Year's Eve.

776
00:50:18.666 --> 00:50:22.462
I'm willing to bet it's whatever
Simon was trying to warn us about.

777
00:50:23.337 --> 00:50:24.881
What do you mean. something big?

778
00:50:25.465 --> 00:50:26.466
I don't know.

779
